<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued April 12 at 7:41PM CDT until April 12 at 8:15PM CDT by NWS Dallas-Fort Worth</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 815 PM CDT
FOR CENTRAL VAN ZANDT...SOUTHERN HOPKINS AND RAINS COUNTIES...
At 741 PM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from Cumby to Grand Saline to Martins Mill, moving east at
40 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Sulphur Springs, Canton, Grand Saline, Van, Emory, Como, Fruitvale
and Edom.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM CDT for north central
Texas.</instruction>
